Let's check for a smaller n. Let's take n=3. Then sum_{k=1}^2 sin^4(kπ/3). sin(π/3)=√3/2, sin²(π/3)=3/4, sin^4(π/3)=9/16. Similarly, sin(2π/3)=√3/2, same value. So sum is 9/16 + 9/16 = 18/16 = 9/8. According to the formula, sum_{k=1}^{2} sin^4(kπ/3) = 3*3/8
